video.title: Bunk'd
video.synopsis: The Ross siblings of Disney's hit series "Jessie" spend a summer full of fun and adventure at Maine's Camp Kikiwaka, where their parents first met.

episodes.synopsis: New roomies and a close encounter with a monster are cause for culture shock when wealthy city kids Emma, Zuri and Ravi arrive at Camp Kikiwaka.
episodes.title: Welcome to Camp Kikiwaka

episodes.synopsis: There's a candy crunch at the camp when Gladys puts a ban on sweets. Ravi misoverhears a conversation and warns Emma about her date with Xander.
episodes.title: Gone Girl

episodes.synopsis: Ravi is starting to take his counselor-in-training duties a little too seriously. To stop Emma and Zuri from arguing, Lou prescribes canoe therapy.
episodes.title: Camp Rules!

episodes.synopsis: When Emma becomes guardian of the spirit stick, she winds up sticking everyone with bad luck. Jorge takes charge when Ravi confesses he can't swim.
episodes.title: Smells Like Camp Spirit

episodes.synopsis: Something's definitely fishy about Zuri and Tiffany's plan to win the camp fishing contest. Fishing buds Emma and Xander wonder if they're compatible.
episodes.title: The Ones That Got Away

episodes.synopsis: Zuri runs into some hang-ups when she keeps her phone against camp rules and tricks Ravi and Tiffany into making a cellphone tower in a totem pole.
episodes.title: Can You Hear Me Now?

episodes.synopsis: Emma feels sorry for the friendless Hazel and decides to be nice to her. A popular TV host comes to camp to chase down the legendary Kikiwaka monster.
episodes.title: Friending with the Enemy

episodes.synopsis: Ravi and Tiffany get proof that the Kikiwaka exists, but no one believes them. Emma, Lou and Hazel compete to be queen of the Kikiwaka Day Festival.
episodes.title: Waka, Waka, Waka!

episodes.synopsis: Jorge is sure he's found the real Santa when the gang gets lost in the woods. Emma has a hard time coming up with the perfect gift to give to Lou.
episodes.title: Secret Santa

episodes.synopsis: While they're away at the annual Counselors' Night Off party, Xander, Lou and Hazel put CIT Ravi in charge, which leads to some very unhappy campers.
episodes.title: Counselors' Night Off

episodes.synopsis: When Jorge starts to act out, it takes a while for the gang to figure out what's wrong. Meanwhile, Lou eats something bad and has a strange reaction.
episodes.title: There's No Place Like Camp

episodes.synopsis: Prankster Luke joins his Ross siblings at camp, much to Ravi's chagrin, but he may come in handy when Camp Champion bullies challenge the Kikiwakans.
episodes.title: Luke's Back

episodes.synopsis: Ravi can't cope when Tiffany gets a crush on him. After Jorge and Zuri sneak into town to shop, Emma and Xander go on a mission to bring them back.
episodes.title: No Escape

episodes.synopsis: Jorge's sure he's seen a UFO crash into the lake, and it's starting to look like he's right. Emma and Ravi are evaluated as counselors-in-training.
episodes.title: Close Encounters of the Camp Kind

episodes.synopsis: Xander and Emma have trouble finding alone time while supervising a camping trip. An easy-assembly jungle gym proves slippery for Ravi and Lou.
episodes.title: Crafted and Shafted

episodes.synopsis: The girls compete to plan Tiffany's first surprise birthday party. Jorge and Ravi take desperate measures to avoid being in the volleyball tournament.
episodes.title: Boo Boo and Birthdays

episodes.synopsis: While Zuri and Emma try to find out what Lou's new crush is hiding, Jorge, Xander and Ravi go on a hunt for the camp's legendary hidden treasure.
episodes.title: For Love and Money

episodes.synopsis: Intellectual Ravi falls for Sasha, a pretty camper who's into extreme sports. Tiffany and Zuri become protective parents after adopting an eagle egg.
episodes.title: Love Is for the Birds

episodes.synopsis: When the little campers are scared by a ghost story about the daughter of the camp's founder, fear starts to spread after some strange happenings.
episodes.title: Bride and Doom

episodes.synopsis: Gladys is terrified Kikiwaka will close next year if she doesn't get more enrollments, so the gang decides to make a cool webcast to reel campers in.
episodes.title: Live from Camp Kikiwaka

episodes.synopsis: When Xander starts acting strangely, Emma suspects he's cheating on her. Best friends Zuri and Tiffany can't stop getting on each other's nerves.
episodes.title: Xander Says Goodbye

episodes.synopsis: Another summer at Kikiwaka begins for Emma, Zuri and Tiffany, who learn that Hazel is now their counselor. Ravi, Xander and Jorge get a new bunkmate.
episodes.title: Griff Is in the House!

episodes.synopsis: The annual dance arrives as a jealous Emma learns that Xander and Lou used to date, while Zuri and Tiffany both hope to dance with Griff.
episodes.title: Dance in My Pants

episodes.synopsis: Emma and Zuri's lackluster job on farm duty results in a sheep escaping. The guys discover that Gladys has been concealing a secret sauna.
episodes.title: Zuri Had a Little Lamb

episodes.synopsis: Zuri envies the freedom of counselors, so Hazel makes her Weasel cabin CIT. Jorge and Griff claim that Wildfire the horse is an artist.
episodes.title: Zuri Weasels Out

episodes.synopsis: Jorge wins a short story contest to meet a famous horror novelist. Xander referees an argument between Emma and Ravi over birdhouse designs.
episodes.title: Queen of Screams

episodes.synopsis: Luke takes Griff and Zuri on a hike to prove he's as responsible as the other CITs. Lou, Xander and Hazel remember the time they first met.
episodes.title: Luke Out Below

episodes.synopsis: A masked figure appears in the woods and campers begin vanishing. Is this revenge on Jorge for a scary prank, or something scarier?
episodes.title: Camp Kiki-slasher

episodes.synopsis: Zuri, Jorge and Tiffany fix up an old tree house, but Lydia and the Weasel campers take it over. The boys challenge the girls at billiards.
episodes.title: Treehouse of Terror

episodes.synopsis: Xander struggles to focus on a music video he's filming because Emma is upset with him. Ravi and Lou forge secret admirer notes to Griff.
episodes.title: Tidal Wave

episodes.synopsis: A thick fog settles over Kikiwaka that robs the campers of their memories and personalities -- and turns Jorge into a snarling creature.
episodes.title: Fog’d In

episodes.synopsis: The campers discover that Griff's misbehavior during Christmas gift-making is related to his lonely holidays in juvenile detention.
episodes.title: How the Griff Stole Christmas

episodes.synopsis: When the campers complain about Murphy's cooking, he challenges them to a culinary competition of making dinner for the whole camp.
episodes.title: Food Fight

episodes.synopsis: Lou's idol Christina Ross pays a visit to Kikiwaka, leading to a case of hero worship. The boys from Grizzly get stuck on a ski lift.
episodes.title: Mother May I?

episodes.synopsis: Zuri, Tiffany and Jorge regret ignoring Ravi's warning not to play in a mud patch. Lou is attracted to Bronson, a manly lighthouse keeper.
episodes.title: Mud Fight

episodes.synopsis: Lou wants to leave camp when she learns that her pet dog has died back at home. Hazel bonds with Ravi and Tiffany thanks to role-playing.
episodes.title: Dog Days of Summer

episodes.synopsis: When new puppy Chuck becomes a menace to the camp, Lou tries sleeping outside with him but he runs away, leading to a surprising discovery.
episodes.title: Bad Dog!

episodes.synopsis: The campers try to pretend that Kikiwaka is a "camp for geniuses" when Tiffany's mother, Dr. Chen, visits. A skunk wreaks havoc on the camp.
episodes.title: Camp Stinky Waka

episodes.synopsis: It's time for the annual Cabin of the Year competition, pitting Woodchuck, Grizzly and Weasel against each other in a series of games.
episodes.title: Cabin vs. Cabin

episodes.synopsis: The campers notice that Lou's dreams often come true. The camp hides Griff from a county officer trying to return him to detention.
episodes.title: Dreams Come True

episodes.synopsis: Emma and Ravi are considered for promotion to full counselors -- then get a chance to prove their skills when a fire breaks out in the cabins.
episodes.title: We Didn’t Start the Fire

episodes.synopsis: Lost near the U.S.-Canadian border, Ravi and Tiffany end up playing matchmaker for border guards who previously dated but broke up.
episodes.title: The Great Escape

episodes.synopsis: The Ross siblings return to camp to find that the burned-out cabins weren't rebuilt and Gladys has absconded with the insurance money.
episodes.title: We Can't Bear It!

episodes.synopsis: Now officially in charge of Camp Kikiwaka as its new owners, the Ross kids must decide which one of them will actually run things.
episodes.title: Let's Bounce!

episodes.synopsis: Lou orders the campers to practice communication skills, so Matteo and Destiny try to help Finn overcome his fear of public speaking.
episodes.title: Take the Cake

episodes.synopsis: Ravi's attempt to use hypnosis as a tool to help Matteo overcome his fears results in a newly -- and problematically -- overconfident camper.
episodes.title: O Sister, Where Art Thou?

episodes.synopsis: After Matteo and Finn confront Ravi about his habit of spying, he comes up with a new strategy: using a drone to be his eye in the sky.
episodes.title: Cav'd In

episodes.synopsis: Emma returns the campers' cell phones and tries to increase the camp's team spirit by urging everyone to use her new app, Campstagram.
episodes.title: By All Memes

episodes.synopsis: Despite the Ross siblings' efforts to make this year's Kikiwaka Lobster Festival the best one ever, the event is a series of disasters.
episodes.title: A Whole Lotta Lobsta

episodes.synopsis: Finding mysterious bones near the camp, Matteo and Finn are sure they've discovered a new species and set a trap to capture a specimen.
episodes.title: No Bones About It

episodes.synopsis: Lou's 10th anniversary at Kikiwaka is approaching, so one group of campers fixes up an old car as a gift while another plans a party.
episodes.title: Finder's Keepers, Lou's a Weeper

episodes.synopsis: Cleaning out the storage room, the camp counselors find a fortune-telling machine that predicts a missing object and a sisterly betrayal.
episodes.title: Reversal of Fortune

episodes.synopsis: Captain Zuri plans for her team of campers to finally defeat the counselors and win the Kikiwaka Cup during the annual camp tournament.
episodes.title: Game of Totems

episodes.synopsis: Zuri is excited to stage a beauty pageant at Camp Kikiwaka but her event receives extremely different reactions from Destiny and Lou.
episodes.title: Toilets and Tiaras

episodes.synopsis: Planning for her future, Lou decides that she will attend college next year, but her mother pressures her to take over the family farm.
episodes.title: Bungle in the Jungle

episodes.synopsis: Opening a mysterious box they find during the camp's Olde Moose Rump Days, the kids are transported back in time to the colonial era.
episodes.title: Gruel and Unusual Punishment

episodes.synopsis: The Kikiwaka campers prepare their entries for blastoff in a model rocket contest, where they'll be judged on speed, safety and altitude.
episodes.title: It's a Blast!

episodes.synopsis: When Emma, Zuri and Ravi get new jobs and learn their mom plans to sell Camp Kikiwaka, they have a hard time figuring out how to tell Lou.
episodes.title: Up, Up, and Away

episodes.synopsis: After buying Camp Kikiwaka from the Ross family for one dollar, Lou becomes the director and welcomes new counselors Noah and Ava.
episodes.title: Who Da Boss? Lou Da Boss!

episodes.synopsis: Finn and Matteo clash over their act for the upcoming camp talent show while Destiny thinks her pageant background will impress Noah.
episodes.title: Kikiwaka's Got Talent

episodes.synopsis: Gwen and Destiny tell an escalating series of lies about a broken window. Noah tries to teach Ava to be more open to new ideas.
episodes.title: Yes, Lies And Tower Escape

episodes.synopsis: Finn proves he's responsible enough to care for Lou's cow Bessie. Destiny and Gwen try to patch things up between Ava and her mother.
episodes.title: An Udder Disaster

episodes.synopsis: Gwen needs a confidence boost when she learns her parents are sending her away to school after summer vacation. Ava discovers a hot spring.
episodes.title: Hot Spring Friend Machine

episodes.synopsis: To raise money for a cleanup of Lake Kikiwaka, Destiny organizes a square dance and invites Noah's archnemesis Austin Justin.
episodes.title: Water Under The Dock

episodes.synopsis: The campers are skeptical when Gwen informs them that her dream effigy doll Cuddles can cause nightmares, but it turns out to be true.
episodes.title: In Your Wildest Screams

episodes.synopsis: Lou allows Hazel, who claims that she has changed, to visit Camp Kikiwaka for a few days. The boys compete for the camp's highest honor.
episodes.title: Inn Trouble

episodes.synopsis: Destiny is going to be the subject of a magazine article about her community service so the campers help her clean up the store – sort of.
episodes.title: Lake Rancid

episodes.synopsis: Gwen befriends a group of campers known for their extreme outdoor exploits and accepts an invitation to go on a challenging hike.
episodes.title: Between A Raccoon And A Hard Place

episodes.synopsis: When the insects become a problem, Matteo tries to invent a better mosquito repellent but steals credit for Gwen's creation instead.
episodes.title: Mo-Squito Mo Problems

episodes.synopsis: Lou tries to lead her campers to a highly unlikely victory in the annual Sportsmanship Games against longtime rival Camp Champion.
episodes.title: Sore Lou-Ser

episodes.synopsis: Gwen is surprised when her older brother Jasper shows up unexpectedly at Kikiwaka and urges her to leave with him.
episodes.title: Lone Wolf

episodes.synopsis: It's time for Renaissance Week and roles are being assigned. Finn is named king of the camp and soon makes his subjects miserable.
episodes.title: Serfs Up-Rising

episodes.synopsis: A cold snap leads to Christmas in July, when the campers discover that Gwen knows nothing about the holiday.
episodes.title: Summer Winter Wonderland

episodes.synopsis: When Camp Champion is flooded by a leak in the pool, Lou invites the camp-less campers to stay at Kikiwaka, which she soon regrets.
episodes.title: Cramped Champions

episodes.synopsis: After finding the diary of Camp Kikiwaka founder Jedediah Swearengen, Lou is blue when she finds out her hero was a traitor.
episodes.title: A Tale Of Two Stackers

episodes.synopsis: Lou gets political when she learns that the mayor, who is running for reelection, is actually a goat. So she runs against him with a sloth.
episodes.title: Whatever Floats Your Goat Boat

episodes.synopsis: Gwen and Matteo are on the case when Camp Kikiwaka's new shaved ice machine is stolen during a heatwave.
episodes.title: Snow Cups And Fisticuffs

episodes.synopsis: Destiny learns that Finn and Matteo celebrated last Thanksgiving without her and tries to make them feel left out by hanging out with other friends.
episodes.title: The S'more, The S'merrier

episodes.synopsis: When Ava's favorite brother Alex visits the camp, he and Lou develop an attraction to each other – one that Ava is not happy about.
episodes.title: Lava At First Sight

episodes.synopsis: Lou organizes a fundraising carnival at the camp and tries to persuade the city council to turn an empty lot into a playground.
episodes.title: Town And Clown Relations

episodes.synopsis: Noah and Destiny notice Matteo sneaking away at night and follow him. Lou joins a women's group that Ava thinks is a coven of witches.
episodes.title: Whisper Toots

episodes.synopsis: Finn is not looking forward to a visit from his mother's boyfriend Dave. Gwen befriends a camper she thinks is actually a fairy.
episodes.title: My Fairy Lady

episodes.synopsis: Lou is invited to deliver a speech at a conference of camp directors. Ava's unusual family birthday tradition leads to a misunderstanding.
episodes.title: Party Pooper

episodes.synopsis: Ava and Destiny realize that the Grizzly Cabin has a bigger bathroom than theirs and scheme to get the boys to switch lodgings with them.
episodes.title: Squatters' Fights

episodes.synopsis: When Lou asks all of the campers to fill out evaluations, Ava worries about the ratings she'll get. Lou also babysits her cousin's child.
episodes.title: Three Stars And A Baby

episodes.synopsis: Lou hopes for a review that will increase business when her travel blogger friend visits the camp but proves difficult to impress.
episodes.title: Manic Moose Day

episodes.synopsis: Barb and Lou swap camp director jobs. But Barb's disciplined, gung-ho approach soon has Kikiwaka's campers plotting to get rid of her.
episodes.title: Breaking Barb

episodes.synopsis: In the second half of the two-part special, Raven and Lou find the campers lost in the Forbidden Forest.
episodes.title: Raven About Bunk'D

episodes.synopsis: Now a fashion designer, Emma drops by Kikiwaka for a visit with old friends — but Ava discovers her glamorous career isn't quite what she claims.
episodes.title: Lou's Still The Boss, But Now There's A Ross

episodes.synopsis: Noah and Ava run Pee-Wee Waka, a new day-care program for kids. Destiny and Finn express different styles while co-hosting the camp radio news show.
episodes.title: Rise Of The Machine

episodes.synopsis: A wealthy heir arrives at Kikiwaka in his customized RV to claim his inherited stake in the camp.
episodes.title: R.V. Having Fun Yet?

episodes.synopsis: Ava volunteers Noah for an aquarium field trip, not realizing he's scared of sea creatures. Destiny fights to save a tree that Parker wants to cut down.
episodes.title: Tentacle Difficulties

episodes.synopsis: When the camp's good-luck charm gets snatched by a bald eagle, bad things start happening around Kikiwaka.
episodes.title: Luck Of The Chuck

episodes.synopsis: Ava tries to take on more responsibility by reviving the Camper of the Week program. Destiny, Finn and Noah misinterpret a parrot's utterances.
episodes.title: Look Who's Squawking

episodes.synopsis: To graduate, Lou enrolls at a community college and takes a chemistry class with a surprising teacher, who has trouble controlling his unruly pupils.
episodes.title: Raucous Science

episodes.synopsis: Noah pretends that he has baton-twirling skills to impress his new crush at the local hospital who happens to be friends with Destiny.
episodes.title: Baton-Man Begins

episodes.synopsis: Ava and Destiny try to plan a scary movie night but they have to take care of Nadine. Lou feels overwhelmed by camp duties and a school assignment.
episodes.title: Everyone's Trap'd

episodes.synopsis: Lou's grandpa comes to visit. Noah invites a reality TV crew to film at the camp but has to manufacture drama to keep the producers' interest.
episodes.title: Pop Pop Poppin' In

episodes.synopsis: Ava and Destiny compete in an underground marble race. Leaving Parker in charge of the camp, Lou uses his RV to travel home with Noah and a stowaway.
episodes.title: Roll Models

episodes.synopsis: During their road trip, Lou and Noah help Matteo stand up to his mother, who wants him to give up science and take over her self-defense class.
episodes.title: Gi Whiz

episodes.synopsis: Lou receives an unexpectedly chilly reception when she drops in on her cousins at the family farm. Parker plans a dance party for his last day in charge.
episodes.title: Dancin' Up A Storm

episodes.synopsis: Ava's official Woodchuck initiation gets canceled due to noise complaints. Parker offers to help Noah plan activities for the Grizzly cabin.
episodes.title: The Great Awkward Bake-Off

episodes.synopsis: Ava volunteers to help her crush bake cookies for a camp fundraiser party but after an embarrassing incident, Destiny intervenes.
episodes.title: Out Of The Doghouse

episodes.synopsis: Destiny rediscovers her passion for clowning when an old friend from the circus visits. Lou asks Parker and Noah to compete in a contest against Barb.
episodes.title: I Won't Let You Clown

episodes.synopsis: When Gwen returns to Camp Kikiwaka for a visit, Noah and Destiny devise a secret scheme to get her to stay and create all sorts of dangerous situations.
episodes.title: Crushin' It

episodes.synopsis: Lou's scary story night brings spooky fun and helps the campers work out their differences when issues arise.
episodes.title: Camp Creepy-Waka

episodes.synopsis: Lou's favorite actress, Melody Chapman, visits Camp Kikiwaka to shadow her as research for an upcoming role.
episodes.title: A Star Is Torn

episodes.synopsis: In need of someone to represent the camp in the Summer Moose Queen pageant, Destiny recruits Parker and Ava for help.
episodes.title: Moose Queens And Possum Kings
